.TH PATH 1 "OShell Manual"
.SH NAME
path \- set shell search path
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B path
[dir1 dir2 ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Set the shell's internal search path for external commands. This path is separate from the system PATH environment variable.
.TP
.B path
Clear the path (no directories to search).
.TP
.B path dir1 dir2 ...
Set path to given directories, searched in order.
.SH NOTES
The shell maintains its own internal path list, not inherited from the environment. The default path is /bin.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
path /bin /usr/bin /usr/local/bin
path
.fi
